description:
&lt;p&gt;Secondment / Fixed term contract – 12 months&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Royal Cornwall Hospitals NHS Trust are transforming the way we both document the care we deliver, and manage the flow of patients through our hospitals..&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are planning an ambitious expansion of our eHealth Programme. In particular the eObservations and eNotes Projects.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are seeking Healthcare Professionals with a strong interest in IT systems, a passion for improving patient safety, and a desire to reduce the burden of paperwork on frontline colleagues. In addition to assisting with the setup and deployment of new systems, the successful applicant will play a strong role in educating clinical staff in their use, in both clinical and classroom based settings.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;These are 3 positions, - 2 full time and 1 part time, which are on a 12month Fixed Term / Secondment basis.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;If you’re excited by the use of digital applications within the NHS and would like an informal chat, please contact Ian Nicholls.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Interview via Microsoft Teams is an option.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Ian Nicholls, eHealth Transformation Manager.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Email – iannicholls@nhs.net Phone: 01872 254592 / 07590 679690&lt;/p&gt;
